            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab><persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/237">Enrico
                            III</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperatore</rs> conferma a dominus <persName
                            key="#Abbots" ref="#people/238">Teuzo</persName> venerabilis <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/131">beatorum martyrum
                            Christi Anthimi et Sebastiani</orgName> quod a bone memorie <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/14">Carolo</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperatore</rs> constructum est in <rs
                            key="#Comitatus">comitato</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/174">Clusino</geogName>
                        <placeName key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/316">loco qui dicitur Vallis
                            Starcia</placeName>, (…) predecessorum nostrorum <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">precepta</rs>, regum videlicet et
                        imperatorum <persName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/14">Caroli</persName>, <persName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/118">Lodouuici</persName> et <persName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/9">Lottarii</persName> et trium <persName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/173 #people/239 #people/7">Ottonum</persName> (…). Conferma
                        perciò i beni del monastero cioè: <rs key="#Curtes">corte</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#places/409"><geogName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#estates/186"><orgName
                                    key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                                    ref="#juridical_persons/169">Sancte Marie que dicitur Mater
                                    ecclesia</orgName></geogName></placeName>, cum <rs
                            key="#Baptismal_churches">plebibus</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Baptismal_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/167">Sancti Salvatoris</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Baptismal_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/168">Sancti Iohannis Baptiste</orgName> et
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/171">Sancte Christine</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/410">Caio</placeName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/170">Sancti Marci</orgName> cum omnibus
                        pertinentiis et aiacentiis suis; <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/200">Sancte Marie</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches">Buble</placeName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/172">Sancti Gregorii</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/173">Sancti Petri</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/411">Gre</placeName>; et <geogName
                            ref="#estates/177"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><placeName key="#Landed_possessions">Adrina</placeName></geogName>
                        et <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cipolonam</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/412">Cignanum</placeName> cum omnibus pertinentiis et
                        aiacentiis suis; ecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/174">Sancti Desiderii</orgName> infra <rs
                            key="#Cities">civitatem</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities #Churches" ref="#places/164">Senensem</placeName> et
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/175">Sancti Adriani</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches">Larciano</placeName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/176">Sanctum Iustum</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/413">Guistrigona</placeName>, <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/177">Sanctum Laurentium</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/414">Corno</placeName>, <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/178">Sanctum Stefanum</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches">Monte</placeName> cum omnibus pertinentiis et aiacentiis
                        suis; <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/181">Sanctum Petrum</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/415">Monticellum</placeName> in <rs
                            key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/83">Florentino</geogName> et
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/182">Sanctum Petrum</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/429">Buita</placeName>, <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >corte</rs> de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/176"><placeName key="#Curtes" ref="#places/398">Valle
                                Fabrice</placeName></geogName> et <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/416">Turrita</placeName> et ecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/183">Sancti Iohannis</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/417">Piscaria</placeName>, <rs
                            key="#Fisheries">anguillaria</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fisheries" ref="#places/418"
                            >Mortaria</placeName> cum barcariis et pertinentiis suis; ecclesiam
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/193">Sancte Marie</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/143">Arcione</placeName>, <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/194">Sanctum Petrum</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/419">Quintiano</placeName> et triginta <rs
                            key="#Saltworks">salinas</rs> in <placeName
                            key="#Saltworks #Sea_salt #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/420">Campo Albiniano</placeName> et ecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/195">Sancte Severe</orgName>, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> que nuncupatur <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/292">Perito</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/427">Oliveto</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Casalia">casale</rs> iuxta <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers #Casalia">Osa</placeName>, <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >corte</rs> de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/188"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/421">Arena</placeName></geogName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/196">Sanctum Liberum</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/66">Pisa</placeName> cum omnibus suis
                        pertinentiis; <rs key="#Curtes">corte</rs> de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/187"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/422">Cellena</placeName></geogName> et <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Castle #Churches"
                            >Lavinum</placeName> cum ecclesiis et <rs key="#Castle">castello</rs>
                        cum una parte de <rs key="#Mountains">monte</rs> usque ad cacumen ipsius,
                            <rs key="#Castle">castrum</rs> etiam de <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/423">Avignone</placeName> cum omnibus suis pertinentiis et
                        aiacentiis; <rs key="#Castle">castrum</rs> super <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            ref="#places/424">Sarturianella</placeName> in <rs key="#Comitatus"
                            >comitatu</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/175">Senensi</geogName> integrum
                        cum medietate ad eum pertinentium; <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        quoque <placeName key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/425"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                                ref="#juridical_persons/197">Sancti Thome
                            apostoli</orgName></placeName> (quod) <persName key="#Abbots"><name
                                ref="Tao">Taio</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> construxit in <rs key="#Fines">finibus</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fines" ref="#estates/185">Pistoriensibus</geogName>
                        confirmamus eidem venerabili loco secundum quod senior noster <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/7">Otto</persName> bone memorie <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus et <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke" ref="#people/3">Hugo</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchio</rs> ordinaverunt, ea videlicet ratione ut
                        abbas qui pro tempore fuerit habeat potestatem ibidem ordinandi monachis et
                        ipsum locum prout ei oportunum visum fuerit; <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/198">Sanctum Antimum</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/414">Locornio</placeName>; <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >Poiolo</placeName>; confirmamus adque imperiali auctoritate
                        corroboramus predicte ecclesie omnem hereditatem <persName><name ref="Hugo"
                                >Ugonis</name></persName> filii bone memorie item <persName><name
                                ref="Hugo de Sciscano">Ugonis</name></persName> de <placeName
                            ref="#places/426">Sciscano</placeName> que illi provenerat ex parte
                        genitoris et genitricis sue; confirmamus similiter prefato monasterio omnem
                        hereditatem <persName><name ref="Corbulinus">Corbulini</name></persName>
                        filii bone memorie <persName><name ref="Maria">Marie</name></persName> que
                        data est predicte ecclesie; <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs> quoque
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/199">Sancti Brasii</orgName> de <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/430">Cornieto</placeName>. Hec omnia
                        suprascripta confirmamus prenominato cenobio sicut continetur in preceptis
                        antecessorum nostrorum et in hoc nostro sunt augmentata, videlicet cum
                        omnibus rebus mobilibus et inmobilibus, cum plebibus, cellulis, castris,
                        domibus, edificiis, servis, anciliis, aldiis et famulis utriusque sexus,
                        libellariis, precariis, cartulariis, massaritiis, campis, vineis, pratis,
                        pascuis, silvis, aquis aquarumque decursibus, piscationibus, venationibus,
                        montibus, alpibus, vallibus, planietibus, salectis, olivetis, cannetis,
                        molendinis, cultis et incultis; confirmamus etiam (…) <rs key="#Decima"
                            >decimas</rs> et primitias de suis hominibus secundum <rs
                            key="#Papal_concession">privilegia apostolicorum Romane sedis</rs> et
                        precepta predecessorum nostrorum imperatorum. Confirmamus quoque ut idem
                        venerabile monasterium quinque <rs
                            key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities">advocatores</rs> liceat
                        habere; illis autem adiungimus XII liberos homines cum quibus rem prelibati
                        monasterii sacramento aquirant et defendant ut nullum tortum malli adiciant.
                        Precipientes insuper iubemus ut nullus episcopus dux marchio comes vicecomes
                        sculdascio nullaque imperii nostri magna parvaque persona predictum
                        venerabilem abbatem vel eius successores aut monachos ibidem deo famulantes
                        de prenominatis cortibus et decimis primitiis vel <rs key="#Slave"
                            >familiis</rs> utriusque sexus seu de omnibus supradictis rebus
                        inquietare aut molestare sive disvestire sine legali iudicio temerario ausu
                        presumat aut <rs key="#Teloneum">teloneum</rs> sive aliquam publicam
                        functionem ab eis exigat nullumque <rs key="#Fodrum">fodrum</rs> vel censum
                        aut paratam persolvere cogantur, sed liceat illis sub nostra <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">tuitione et defensione</rs> quiete et
                        pacifice vivere (…). Conferma infine la licenza ai monaci di scegliere fra
                        loro l’abate. Stabilisce una pena auri obrizi libras mille, medietatem
                        camere nostre et medietatem prefato abbati aut eis successoribus; e fa
                        apporre il proprio sigillo. Recognitio del <rs key="#Chancellor"
                            >cancelliere</rs>
                        <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Obizo">Opizzo</name></persName> ad
                        vicem dell’<rs key="#Archbishops">arcivescovo</rs> e <rs
                            key="#Archchancellor">arcicancelliere</rs>
                        <persName key="#Archchancellor #Archbishops"><name ref="Ermannus"
                                >Ermanno</name></persName>. Actum
                        <placeName>Chouphungin</placeName>. </ab>
                        </div>
                    </div>
